description: trait

NEW_SELECT_VALS: select values. disregard previous value selection
AND_SELECT_VALS: this value selection condition AND the previous condition/s must be fulfilled
OR_SELECT_VALS: this value selection condition OR the previous condition/s must be fulfilled
NEW_SELECT_ROWS: select rows. disregard previous row selection
AND_SELECT_ROWS: this row selection condition AND the previous condition/s must be fulfilled
OR_SELECT_ROWS: this row selection condition OR the previous condition/s must be fulfilled
NEW_SELECT_COLS: select columns. disregard previous column selection
AND_SELECT_COLS: this column selection condition AND the previous condition/s must be fulfilled
OR_SELECT_COLS: this column selection condition OR the previous condition/s must be fulfilled
MODIFY: modify settings, metadata, format, headers, values or create new columns
TRIM: trim row/col selection based on val selection.
IS_ANY: is any value (use to reset selection)
IS_YN: is a value representing yes or no
IS_FIRST: is the first value (of multiple values)
IS_LAST: is the last value (of multiple values)
ADD: append a string to the value (coerce to string if needed)
SORT: sort values based on the selected column(s)
TO_YN: convert to yes or no value
ANY: select whole row if ANY value in the selected columns fulfills the condition
ALL: select whole row if ALL values in the selected columns fulfill the condition
IDX: select whole row if the index of the row fulfills the condition
STRICT: use strict comparison for selection condition (eg: case sensitive, strict typing)
SAVE_SELECTION: save current selection with given <name>. load using: "$load = <name>
LOAD_SELECTION: load a saved selection of rows/values (boolean mask). save using: "$save = <name>
DIFF: change if and how the difference between the old and new dataframe is shown
METADATA: modify the metadata of the selected rows/values
TAG_METADATA: add a tag of the currently selected column(s) in the form of "\n@<selected col>: <value>" to the column named "meta"
COLOR: change the color of the selected values
BACKGROUND_COLOR: change the background color of the selected values
ALIGN: change the alignment of the selected values
WIDTH: change the width of the selected values
CSS: use css to format the selected values
COLS: modify the colnames of the selected columns
ROWS: modify the values in the selected rows
NEW_COL: create a new column with the selected values
COL_EVAL: when used with the eval operator, evaluates on the whole column
REGEX: use regex for equality and contains operator
